<subSubSection id="8BA45A9B9468FFD6FF4BFB0410BFD803" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C30109109468FFD6FF4BFB0416BFDA08" blockId="5.[151,1437,402,1800]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">
<emphasis id="F1CAD5029468FFD6FF4BFB041544DBA4" bold="true" box="[199,315,1159,1185]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Remarks.</emphasis>
According to the most recent revision of the Chinese species of this genus (
<bibRefCitation id="A72F74E19468FFD6FB35FB0414ACDBC0" author="Miroshnikov, A. I. &amp; Lin, M. - Y." pageId="5" pageNumber="456" pagination="177 - 214" refId="ref23895" refString="Miroshnikov, A. I. &amp; Lin, M. - Y. (2017) The Longicorn Beetle Genus Apatophysis Chevrolat, 1860 (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Apatophyseini) in China, with Preliminary Remarks on its Intrageneric Structure and with Descriptions of Three New Species. Special Bulletin of the Coleopterological Society of Japan, 1, 177 - 214." type="journal article" year="2017">Miroshnikov &amp; Lin 2017</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="04BE72939468FFD6FF69FB281501DBC0" baseAuthorityName="Gebler" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[229,382,1195,1222]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Apatophysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serricornis">
<emphasis id="F1CAD5029468FFD6FF69FB281489DBC0" box="[229,246,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F1CAD5029468FFD6FE8FFB2F1501DBC0" box="[259,382,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">serricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in 
<collectingCountry id="BBA949809468FFD6FDB8FB281608DBC0" box="[564,631,1195,1221]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="017AC7F29468FFD6FD08FB281697DBC0" box="[644,744,1195,1221]" country="China" name="Xinjiang Uygur" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Xinjiang</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="017AC7F29468FFD6FC90FB2F17B1DBC0" box="[796,974,1195,1222]" country="China" name="Nei Mongol" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Inner Mongolia</collectingRegion>
; however, the authors also reported on the two problematic males that are known from one of the southernmost provinces— 
<collectingRegion id="017AC7F29468FFD6FBB4FB4C10C3DBEF" box="[1080,1212,1231,1258]" country="China" name="Guangdong" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Guangdong</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry id="BBA949809468FFD6FB5CFB4C1142DBEC" box="[1232,1341,1231,1257]" name="Mongolia" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
(mainly southern part of the country) and SE 
<collectingCountry id="BBA949809468FFD6FDBAFB7016C3DA08" box="[566,700,1267,1293]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C30109109468FFD6FF4BFA9415A1DA98" blockId="5.[151,1437,402,1800]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">
This highly variable species has been already described several times based on its different forms (
<taxonomicName id="04BE72939468FFD6FA87FA941540DA53" authority="(Gebler, 1845)" baseAuthorityName="Gebler" baseAuthorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Apatophysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tomentosa">
<emphasis id="F1CAD5029468FFD6FA87FA941163DA34" box="[1291,1308,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F1CAD5029468FFD6FAA5FA9B11E3DA34" box="[1321,1436,1304,1329]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">tomentosa</emphasis>
(Gebler, 1845)
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="04BE72939468FFD6FEC0FAB8169DDA53" authority="(Motschulsky, 1860)" baseAuthorityName="Motschulsky" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[332,738,1339,1366]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Apatophysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obtusicollis">
<emphasis id="F1CAD5029468FFD6FEC0FAB81522DA50" box="[332,349,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F1CAD5029468FFD6FEE0FAB81592DA50" box="[364,493,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">obtusicollis</emphasis>
(Motschulsky, 1860)
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="04BE72939468FFD6FD63FAB81041DA50" authority="Semenov, 1901" authorityName="Semenov" authorityYear="1901" box="[751,1086,1339,1366]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Apatophysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mongolica">
<emphasis id="F1CAD5029468FFD6FD63FAB8177FDA50" box="[751,768,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F1CAD5029468FFD6FC83FAB817FADA50" box="[783,901,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">mongolica</emphasis>
Semenov, 1901
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="04BE72939468FFD6FBC7FAB811EADA53" authority="Kadlec, 2006" authorityName="Kadlec" authorityYear="2006" box="[1099,1429,1339,1366]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Apatophysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kadyrbekovi">
<emphasis id="F1CAD5029468FFD6FBC7FAB81023DA50" box="[1099,1116,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F1CAD5029468FFD6FBE7FAB8108BDA50" box="[1131,1268,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">kadyrbekovi</emphasis>
Kadlec, 2006
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="A72F74E19468FFD6FF13FADC151CDA7C" author="Danilevsky, M. L." box="[159,355,1375,1401]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" pagination="7 - 55" refId="ref21854" refString="Danilevsky, M. L. (2008) Apatophysis Chevrolat, 1860 (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae) of Russia and adjacent regions. Studies and Reports of District Museum Prague-East, Taxonomical Series, 4 (1 - 2), 7 - 55." type="journal article" year="2008">Danilevsky 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="A72F74E19468FFD6FEFCFADC16EBDA7C" author="Miroshnikov, A. I. &amp; Lin, M. - Y." box="[368,660,1375,1401]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" pagination="177 - 214" refId="ref23895" refString="Miroshnikov, A. I. &amp; Lin, M. - Y. (2017) The Longicorn Beetle Genus Apatophysis Chevrolat, 1860 (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Apatophyseini) in China, with Preliminary Remarks on its Intrageneric Structure and with Descriptions of Three New Species. Special Bulletin of the Coleopterological Society of Japan, 1, 177 - 214." type="journal article" year="2017">Miroshnikov &amp; Lin 2017</bibRefCitation>
). It also shows a strong sexual dimorphism, which causes additional difficulties in its systematics.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C30109109468FFD6FF4BFA2416DAD970" blockId="5.[151,1437,402,1800]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">
<taxonomicName id="04BE72939468FFD6FF4BFA2415ACDAC4" baseAuthorityName="Gebler" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[199,467,1447,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Apatophysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serricornis">
<emphasis id="F1CAD5029468FFD6FF4BFA2415ACDAC4" box="[199,467,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Apatophysis serricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, unlike some other representatives of the genus, is most likely a nocturnal species (at least 
<specimenCount id="D5B8C2999468FFD6FF5CFA4F150ADAE0" box="[208,373,1483,1510]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
have been recorded as attracted to a light trap by 
<bibRefCitation id="A72F74E19468FFD6FC18FA4810F9DAE0" author="Namhaidorzh, B." box="[916,1158,1483,1509]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" pagination="495 - 538" refId="ref24062" refString="Namhaidorzh, B. (1972) On the fauna of longicorn beetles (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae) of the Mongolian People's Republic. Insects of Mongolia, 1, 495 - 538. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1972">Namhaidorzh (1972))</bibRefCitation>
and its bionomy remains largely unknown. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="A72F74E19468FFD6FE74FA6C16B4D90C" author="Danilevsky, M. L." box="[504,715,1519,1545]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" pagination="7 - 55" refId="ref21854" refString="Danilevsky, M. L. (2008) Apatophysis Chevrolat, 1860 (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae) of Russia and adjacent regions. Studies and Reports of District Museum Prague-East, Taxonomical Series, 4 (1 - 2), 7 - 55." type="journal article" year="2008">Danilevsky (2008)</bibRefCitation>
, it is ecologically associated with desert and semi-desert habitats of different 
<typeStatus id="1C05B7B29468FFD6FE90F9971528D92B" box="[284,343,1556,1582]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">types</typeStatus>
(both sandy and clay soils). Larvae develop in roots of probably different desert shrubs and trees, however, development only in 
<taxonomicName id="04BE72939468FFD6FE76F9B416BED957" authority="Bunge" authorityName="Bunge" box="[506,705,1591,1618]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Haloxylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F1CAD5029468FFD6FE76F9B41610D954" box="[506,623,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Haloxylon</emphasis>
Bunge
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="04BE72939468FFD6FD5DF9B417FCD957" box="[721,899,1591,1618]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Amaranthaceae</taxonomicName>
) was confirmed (
<bibRefCitation id="A72F74E19468FFD6FBC0F9B4116DD954" author="Danilevsky, M. L." box="[1100,1298,1591,1617]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" pagination="125 - 129" refId="ref21672" refString="Danilevsky, M. L. (1988) Subfamily Apatophyseinae. In: Svacha, P. &amp; Danilevsky, M. L. (Eds.), Cerambycoid larvae of Europe and Soviet Union (Coleoptera, Cerambycoidea). Part II. Acta Universitatis Carolinae, Biologica, 31 (3 - 4), 125 - 129." type="journal article" year="1988">Danilevsky 1988</bibRefCitation>
). Adults are active from June to August (
<bibRefCitation id="A72F74E19468FFD6FE5FF9D816E6D970" author="Danilevsky, M. L." box="[467,665,1627,1653]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" pagination="7 - 55" refId="ref21854" refString="Danilevsky, M. L. (2008) Apatophysis Chevrolat, 1860 (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae) of Russia and adjacent regions. Studies and Reports of District Museum Prague-East, Taxonomical Series, 4 (1 - 2), 7 - 55." type="journal article" year="2008">Danilevsky 2008</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C30109109468FFD6FF4BF90310BFD803" blockId="5.[151,1437,402,1800]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">
<materialsCitation id="73D6034D9468FFD6FF4BF90310C3D803" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3418264354" collectionCode="HNHM" country="Mongolia" location="Omnogovi aimag" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Omnogovi">
<collectingMethod id="1AFF71079468FFD6FF4BF90310BDD99F" box="[199,1218,1663,1690]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">We have not collected any individual of this species despite the frequent use of light traps</collectingMethod>
in the region of its occurrence. This is probably explained by the fact that our research was conducted in a rather late season, in the last quarter of July. Most of the Mongolian records relate to the second half of June. The depicted female comes from the Kaszab’s material (
<collectionCode id="A5AF91D59468FFD6FE1BF968158DD800" box="[407,498,1771,1797]" country="Hungary" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" name="Hungarian Natural History Museum (Termeszettudomanyi Muzeum)" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">HNHM</collectionCode>
), and it was collected in southern 
<collectingCountry id="BBA949809468FFD6FCE2F96817A4D800" box="[878,987,1771,1797]" name="Mongolia" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="017AC7F29468FFD6FC66F96E10CCD803" box="[1002,1203,1771,1800]" country="Mongolia" name="Omnogovi" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Ömnögovi aimag</collectingRegion>
)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
